Step 10 — Create GitHub Actions Workflow

Inside VS Code create folder:

.github

Inside it create folder:

workflows

Inside that create file:

ci.yml

Final structure:

python-app
│
├── app.py
├── requirements.txt
└── .github
      └── workflows
            └── ci.yml
Step 11 — Write GitHub Actions Pipeline

Open ci.yml

Paste:

name: CI Pipeline

on:
  push:
    branches: [ main ]

jobs:
  build:

    runs-on: ubuntu-latest

    steps:

    - name: Checkout code
      uses: actions/checkout@v3

    - name: Setup Python
      uses: actions/setup-python@v4
      with:
        python-version: '3.10'

    - name: Install dependencies
      run: pip install -r requirements.txt

    - name: Run Application
      run: python app.py

Save.

Step 12 — Push Workflow File

Run:

git add .
git commit -m "added CI pipeline"
git push
Step 13 — Check Pipeline

Open GitHub repository.

Click:

Actions

You will see:

